  "prompt": "How can I tell if a guy likes me or is just using me?",
  "response": "Determining whether a guy genuinely likes you or is using you can be challenging, but there are several signs to consider:\n\n1. **Consistent Communication**: If he regularly reaches out to talk or text and shows genuine interest in how your day is going, it's a positive sign. If communication feels one-sided or sporadic, it might indicate a lack of genuine interest.\n\n2. **Investment of Time**: A guy who likes you will make an effort to spend time with you. If he often makes excuses and doesn't prioritize time together, he may not be serious about you.\n\n3. **Interest in Your Life**: Pay attention to whether he asks about your interests, family, and future plans. A guy who genuinely likes you will want to know more about you and what matters to you.\n\n4. **Respect for Boundaries**: A respectful guy will be mindful of your boundaries and comfort levels. If he pushes for physical intimacy or rushes things without your consent, it might be a red flag.\n\n5. **Future Plans**: If he talks about spending time together in the future or includes you in his long-term plans, it's a good indication of his interest. If he avoids discussions about the future, he may not view the relationship as serious.\n\n6. **Supportive Behavior**: A guy who genuinely cares will be there for you during tough times and celebrate your successes with you. If he only seems to be around when it\u2019s convenient for him, that could indicate self-serving motives.\n\n7. **Honesty and Openness**: A genuine connection is built on trust and openness. If he shares details about his life and feelings, it may show that he values your relationship. If he is secretive or avoids deeper conversations, it might signal ulterior motives.\n\n8. **Listen to Your Intuition**: Trust your gut feelings. If something feels off or you sense that he might not have your best interests at heart, take those feelings seriously.\n\n9. **Feedback from Friends**: Sometimes, friends can offer valuable perspective. If your friends express concern about his behavior or a lack of investment, consider their opinions.\n\n10. **Watch for Mixed Signals**: Pay attention to his actions versus what he says. Sometimes, people can say they like you but act in ways that suggest otherwise.\n\nUltimately, clear communication is crucial. If you're unsure about his intentions, consider discussing your feelings and asking about his perspective on the relationship. A mature guy will appreciate your honesty and be willing to have that conversation.",
